jobs_results.description:
Exciting career opportunity to be involved in digital projects as Business Analyst Manager in the Financial Services.

Mandatory Skill(s)
• A Degree holder in Computer Science or Information Systems or Information Technology;
• At least 8 years of working experience within Financial Services or Insurance domain;
• Minimum 6 years of progressive experience as a Business Analyst / Manager;
• Experienced in end to end implementation of digital projects;
• Strong analytical skills and prior experience in user experience design;
• Experienced in mentoring and leading a team;
• Excellent interpersonal and communication skills to interact with business, users and vendors at different levels;

Desirable Skill(s)
• PMP / PRINCE2 Certified;

Responsibilities
• Responsible for managing requirements of the users for digital implementations;
• Act as a liaison between business users and technology teams;
• Develop functional and technical specifications for the technical team;
• Monitor project... status and liaise with business / vendors in giving solutions to resolve problems;
• Manage functional testing and provide support during User Acceptance Testing ;
• Responsible for managing the user change requests/enhancements;
• Liaise with various stakeholders to ensure compliance with risk and security policies

Our client in banking industry is seeking for highly motivated Production Support Analyst, to be a part of their Technology and Operations team.

Mandatory Skill(s)
• Degree in Computer Science, Business Information Technology or related disciplines;
• Experience in incident and problem management;
• Knowledge on Site Reliability Engineering (SRE) best practices and able to adhere to SRE guidelines in the work;
• Experience in production support and monitoring tools;
• Good in understanding internal process with a passion to seek improvements;
• Good analytical skills with excellent communication;
• Good problem solver to investigate the root cause analysis.

Desirable Skill(s)
• ITIL certified;
• Experience in banking industry.

Responsibilities
• Perform work in shifts to provide 24/7 on-site or on-call support;
• Handle Incident and Problem management;
• Analyse issues and problems for critical systems;
• Provide root cause analysis techniques to determine cause and resolve complex... system issues;
• Perform post-resolution follow-ups to ensure problems have been adequately resolved;
• Work closely with key stakeholders, including management, development teams, end users, and unit leaders and communicate application problems and issues;
• Collaborate with business operations and technology partners at a regional and/or global level daily;
• Work with onsite and offshore teams across multiple technologies/applications;
• Responsible for continuous improvement of the system, eq. removal of TOIL, job automation, performance tuning;
• Proactive management of production services by measuring and monitoring availability, latency, throughput, user journeys and overall system health
